<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-25T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/105</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-25T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 25,
                                            1918, 7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>733. Please report whether following statement alleged to have been
                                made by <persName corresp="#p_MGCGE1">Mannerheim</persName> is
                                authentic: <pb facs="0873" n="783" xml:id="pg_783"/>
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>The Germans’ victorious and mighty army landed in Finland to
                                        help against the infamous Bolsheviks, and to help the
                                        friendship the Finnish people have always had for the noble
                                        Kaiser and mighty German people. Fighting shoulder to
                                        shoulder with the great merman army the Finnish army should
                                        be imbued with the discipline that has brought that army
                                        from victory to victory. I greet the brave German troops and
                                        hope that every Finn will realize the great sacrifice of the
                                        noble German people who are helping them in an hour when
                                        every man is needed on the western front.</p></quote></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>